<font color="#FF0000">BAD RELATIONSHIPS,GREAT PEOPLE</font><br>
<tt>Thu Jul 31  7:02:15 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Hi, I wanted to add to what Nancy was saying about bad relationships.  I have asked a lot of people who are abused or in bad relationships, &quot;why you?&quot;  The answer is always about their weaknesses, stupidity or problems.<br><br>
I'm worried about this.  It is part of a whole, blame the victim, view.  But now, it is the person who is being abused who is blaming herself (or himself).<br><br>
What I would like to add here is that their partner often becomes interested in them because of their strengths and talents, not because of their weaknesses.   That abuser often starts out showing a lot of respect and appreciation.   It feels like a really good relationship.  This makes it hard to tell at the beginning what is going to happen.    <br><br>
The control that Nancy was talking about is often key to the relationship becoming bad.  It feels like the partner is trying to keep the wonderful person to themselves.  <br><br>
It may seem great to have someone care where you go and want to be with you all the time.  However, if they are trying to keep you with them and keep you away from others, this is a danger sign to pay attention to. <br><br>
What do you think?<br><br>
 
<p><code>--   (Meryle) </code><p>


